"1457":"1457","1477":"1477","Abt 1457":"about 1457","Ebor, Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Pole","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Leicestershire): variant of   Paul   or   Poole  .","Americanized form of German   Pohle   or   Pohl  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Poles","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Angelo, Livio, Primo, Santo.","English and Welsh: variant of   Pole   and   Powell   + genitival or excrescent <i>-s</i>.","Italian (Friuli and Veneto): probably a derivative of the personal name   Polo  . It is also found in Slovenia."]},{"name":"Paul","meanings":["English, French, German, Dutch, Swedish, West Indian (mainly Haiti, also e.g. Saint Lucia), and African (mainly Nigeria and Tanzania): from the personal name <i>Paul</i> (from Latin <i>Paulus</i> ‘small’), which has always been popular in Christendom. It was the name adopted by the Pharisee Saul of Tarsus after his conversion to Christianity on the road to Damascus in about  AD  34. He was a most energetic missionary to the Gentiles in the Roman Empire, and played a very significant role in establishing Christianity as a major world religion. The name was borne also by numerous other early Christian saints. It is also occasionally borne by Jews; the reasons for this are not clear. In North America, the English form of the surname has absorbed many cognates from other languages and their patronymics and other derivatives, e.g. Greek   Pavlis  , Slovenian   Pavel   and <b>Pavlič</b> (see   Pavlic  ), Polish <b>Paweł</b> (see   Pawel  ) and   Pawlicki  , Assyrian/Chaldean   Polous   and   Polus  . In France, this surname is most common in Brittany (see 2 below).","Breton (mainly Finistère): from a Frenchified form of the personal name <i>Paol</i>, Breton form of   Paul  .","Irish: shortened Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Phóil</b> ‘son of Paul’. Compare   McFall  ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"T. Pole was born about 1457, in Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"Abt 1457–":"umbes 1457–Surnud","1477–1513":"1477–1513","1457–Male":"1457–Surnud","1513":"1513","1457":"1457","1477":"1477","Abt 1457":"umbes 1457","Ebor, Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1457–":"noin 1457–Kuollut","1477–1513":"1477–1513","1457–Male":"1457–Kuollut","1513":"1513","1457":"1457","1477":"1477","Abt 1457":"noin 1457","Ebor, Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1457–":"environ 1457–Décédé","1477–1513":"1477–1513","1457–Male":"1457–Décédé","1513":"1513","1457":"1457","1477":"1477","Abt 1457":"environ 1457","Ebor, Yorkshire, England":"Everwyck, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"T. Pole est né environ 1457, à Everwyck, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Il a eu au moins 1 fille."},"de":{"Abt 1457–":"um 1457–Verstorben","1477–1513":"1477–1513","1457–Male":"1457–Verstorben","1513":"1513","1457":"1457","1477":"1477","Abt 1457":"um 1457","Ebor, Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"T. Pole wurde um 1457 in Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom geboren. Er hatte mindestens 1 Tochter."},"ht":{"Abt 1457–":"about 1457–Desede","1477–1513":"1477–1513","1457–Male":"1457–Desede","1513":"1513","1457":"1457","1477":"1477","Abt 1457":"about 1457","Ebor, Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, Angletè, United Kingdom"},"hu":{"Abt 1457–":"1457 körül–elhunyt","1477–1513":"1477–1513","1457–Male":"1457–elhunyt","1513":"1513","1457":"1457","1477":"1477","Abt 1457":"1457 körül","Ebor, Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, Anglia, United Kingdom"},"id":{"Abt 1457–":"sekitar 1457–Telah Meninggal","1477–1513":"1477–1513","1457–Male":"1457–Telah Meninggal","1513":"1513","1457":"1457","1477":"1477","Abt 1457":"sekitar 1457","Ebor, Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, Inggris, United Kingdom"},"it":{"Abt 1457–":"circa 1457–Deceduto","1477–1513":"1477–1513","1457–Male":"1457